Web search results for query: "Paddle Billing "Paddle.Checkout.open" customer email discount parameter pass dynamically javascript"

Links: [{"title":"Paddle.Checkout.open() - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/paddlejs/methods/paddle-checkout-open"},{"title":"Pass a discount code to Paddle.js - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/changelog/2023/pass-discount-code-paddlejs"},{"title":"Build an overlay checkout - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/build/checkout/build-overlay-checkout"},{"title":"HTML data attributes - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/paddlejs/html-data-attributes"},{"title":"Pass checkout settings - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/build/checkout/set-up-checkout-default-settings"},{"title":"Prefill checkout properties - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/build/checkout/prefill-checkout-properties"},{"title":"Paddle.js - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/paddlejs/overview"},{"title":"Paddle Checkout - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/concepts/sell/self-serve-checkout"},{"title":"Paddle checkout","url":"https://docs.partnerstack.com/docs/paddle-checkout"},{"title":"Update an open checkout using Paddle.js - Paddle Developer","url":"https://developer.paddle.com/changelog/2023/update-checkout-method-paddlejs"}]

Based on the search results, here's information about passing customer email and discount parameters dynamically to `Paddle.Checkout.open()`:

## Customer Email Parameter

You can pass an email for the customer, but you can't use it if you're passing an id. The email field is part of the customer object in the `Paddle.Checkout.open()` method.

## Discount Parameters

You can pass a discount code to apply to the checkout to prepopulate a discount, passing either discountCode or discountId.

## Dynamic Passing in JavaScript

The discountCode parameter and data-discount-code HTML data attribute let you pass a discount code instead of needing to make an additional call to the API or use the Paddle dashboard to get its ID.

Here's an example of dynamically passing both parameters:

```javascript
var itemsList = [
  {
    priceId: 'pri_01gm81eqze2vmmvhpjg13bfeqg',
    quantity: 1
  }
];

Paddle.Checkout.open({
  items: itemsList,
  customer: {
    email: "customer@example.com"
  },
  discountCode: "DYNAMIC_CODE"
});
```

You can also use the Paddle.Checkout.updateCheckout() method to update discount and customer information, passing discountId or discountCode along with items to swap or remove the discount on an open checkout.


